ts unhealthily.\n\n- Candidate B keeps calm in a crisis.\n- Candidate B is known to be 100% reliable.\n- Candidate B is good at assessing weather conditions.\n- Candidate B has excellent computer skills.\n- Candidate B is regarded as pretentious.\n- Candidate B sometimes adopts the wrong tone when communicating.\n\n- Candidate C can make correct decisions quickly.\n- Candidate C has difficulty communicating ideas.\n- Candidate C is regarded as egocentric.\n- Candidate C is not very willing to further his education.\n- Candidate C puts concern for others above everything.\n- Candidate C has excellent attention skills.\n\n- Candidate D responds to unexpected events adequately.\n- Candidate D can concentrate very well.\n- Candidate D solves problems extremely well.\n- Candidate D takes responsibility seriously.\n- Candidate D is considered moody.\n- Candidate D is regarded as a loner.\n\nThus we have some additional info not previously mentioned: For C, \"puts concern for others above everything\" and \"excellent attention skills\". For D, \"moody\" and \"loner\". For B, \"pretentious\" and \"wrong tone\". For A, \"unfriendly\" and \"eats unhealthily\". Also we have \"excellent attention skills\" for C, which is a strength.\n\nNow we need to respond to the discussion. The last agent (agent_1) answered the missing info: no data for A reliability/calmness, B teamwork strengths, D teamwork strengths. They also voted Candidate C.\n\nWe as agent_3 should add any additional info we have that addresses those gaps, or provide further assessment, maybe ask further questions about missing info we still lack (e.g., A reliability, D teamwork). But we have no data on those. However we have additional info about C's concern for others and attention skills, which strengthens C. Also we have D's moody and loner, which are weaknesses. Also B's pretentious and wrong tone, which are weaknesses. Also A's unfriendly and unhealthy eating, which are weaknesses.\n\nWe can reinforce that Candi